00:00:42.940 --> 00:00:44.940
It's rice

00:00:51.140 --> 00:00:55.989
With the top and bottom cut off of our can, we want to take a balloon and stretch it over the mouth of the can.

00:00:56.090 --> 00:00:59.680
The first step is we're going to blow the balloon up almost as much as it will go.

00:01:05.570 --> 00:01:10.449
Now it's stretched out, and we'll have an easier time fitting over the can. We want to cut it about

00:01:10.910 --> 00:01:15.489
1/2 of the total balloon length down, not at the very widest part, but just above that.

00:01:17.690 --> 00:01:21.699
Stretching the balloon over the mouth is going to be a lot easier if you have another pair of hands to help.

00:01:26.899 --> 00:01:32.139
Once it's stretched into place, use a little bit of electrical tape around the edge to keep it from coming off.

00:01:45.460 --> 00:01:48.690
Now if your goal is just to make yourself a miniature drum, congratulations! You're done.

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:51.480
However, we're trying to make a laser light show.

00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:57.179
So we're not quite there yet. The next step is we need to attach about a one-inch square piece of mirror to our latex

00:01:57.180 --> 00:02:02.400
balloon. Most types of mirrors are made from glass and it's hard to cut them, but this type is made from plastic because it's designed

00:02:02.400 --> 00:02:05.459
to be used in the shower. I guess it's protection in case it drops.

00:02:05.979 --> 00:02:09.419
Since its plastic, we're gonna see if we can cut through it and just make a piece about that size.

00:02:18.459 --> 00:02:20.909
Now that the fact that it's cracking like that gives me an idea.

