Just not where I thought it was going to.

00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:43.440
There we go.

00:02:46.209 --> 00:02:50.699
I'm gonna try throwing this in the vise and see if that will help give me a cleaner edge to break along.

00:02:59.800 --> 00:03:02.969
There we have it, I'm just going use some sandpaper to clean at the edges

00:03:08.910 --> 00:03:11.359
There we have it. Our one-inch square piece of mirror.

00:03:11.360 --> 00:03:14.690
Now we're just going to attach that to the centre of the balloon using some double-sided tape.

00:03:24.200 --> 00:03:27.519
Reach inside and make sure it's pressed nicely down on there.

00:03:29.330 --> 00:03:31.419
Now we know it's gonna stick, no problem.

00:03:32.270 --> 00:03:36.880
Now with the mirror attached, we have the basis for what we're going to use to make our laser light show work.

00:03:36.880 --> 00:03:41.320
We're going to set this can up in front of a speaker and when the air waves coming out of the speaker hit the rubber,

00:03:41.450 --> 00:03:45.759
it's going to make it vibrate. The laser pointer will be shining right on the mirror and

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:52.659
reflecting onto the wall. As the latex vibrates with the music, the pattern on the wall will move in some sort of spirograph

00:03:52.790 --> 00:03:55.900
patterns that match the vibrations of the sound we listening to.

00:03:56.150 --> 00:04:01.269
